<p>Subtracting Vectors</p>
<p>Multiplying a vector <m>\bf{v}</m> by <m>-1</m> gives a vector <m>-\bf{v}</m> that has the same magnitude as <m>\bf{v}</m> but points in the opposite direction. We define subtraction of two vectors the same way we define subtraction of integers:
<me>\bf{u} - \bf{v} = \bf{u} + (-\bf{v})</me>
That is, to subtract a vector <m>\bf{v}</m>, we add its opposite.</p>

